works.description: While Financial News, a London-based sister publication of The Wall Street Journal, stated lately that the properties on Hong Kong’s Severn Road cost more per square foot than those anywhere else, The Wealth Report 2011 by London-based property broker Knight Frank and Citi Private Bank has concluded that Monaco is the world’s most expensive residential location. According to the report, Monaco remains the most expensive residential location in the world, followed by London. For $1 million, a property investor can expect to buy just 15 square meters of luxury real estate in Monaco.
